    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I just got v0.11.6 (upgraded from v0.11.5) and it broke anything that depends on the bundled treesitter stuff.\n\nI just have a ftplugin that auto-detects e.g. lua and that causes the following when opening a .lua file:\n\n```\nError detected while processing BufReadPost Autocommands for \"*\":\nError executing lua callback: /snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:36: BufReadPost Autocommands for \"*\"..FileType Autocommands for \"*\"..function <SNR>1_LoadFTPlugin[20]..script /snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/lua.lua: Vim(runtime):E5113:\n Error while calling lua chunk: .../nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:431: Parser could not be created for buffer 1 and language \"lua\"\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'assert'\n        .../nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:431: in function 'start'\n        /snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/lua.lua:2: in main chunk\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_cmd'\n        /snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:36: in function </snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:35>\n        [C]: in function 'pcall'\n        vim/shared.lua: in function <vim/shared.lua:0>\n        [C]: in function '_with'\n        /snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:35: in function </snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:10>\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function '_with'\n        /snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:35: in function </snap/nvim/4652/usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:10>\n```\n\nIf I manually add the correct runtime path, it works:\n\n`vim.opt.runtimepath:append('/snap/nvim/4652/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/nvim')`\n\n... so ... it's a packaging error?",
